      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLASSIC ETHICS (7) jumped from a low draw and boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten a neck (35.87) behind Intrepid Eagle at Richmond. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Top chance in this line up. BEAUTIFUL MAGPIE (1) recorded a Grade 4/5 win two back then missed the frame last time at Wentworth Park, but drawn Box 1 this time where she has four wins. Safe beginner and drawn well on the inside. Has the ability and expected to do much better. PINK PANAMA (2) missed the frame last time when sixth (30.97) at Wentworth Park but prior to that had two placings in a row. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Better than last start and can bounce back. LITTLE LINKIN (3) is likely to have admirers.",
